quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  32,21,"And We shall indeed make them taste the smaller punishment before the greater punishment, so that they may return."
  32,22,"And who is more unjust than one who is preached to from the verses his Lord, then he turns away from them? We will indeed take revenge from the guilty."
  32,23,"And indeed We bestowed the Book to Moosa, therefore have no doubt in its acquisition, and made it a guidance for the Descendants of Israel."
  32,24,"And We made some leaders among them, guiding by Our command, when they had persevered; and they used to accept faith in Our signs."
  32,25,"Indeed your Lord will judge between them on the Day of Resurrection concerning the matters in which they used to differ."
  32,26,"And did they not obtain guidance by the fact that We did destroy many generations before them, so now they walk in their houses? Indeed in this are signs; so do they not heed?"
  32,27,"And do they not see that We send the water to the barren land and produce crops with it, so their animals and they themselves eat from it? So do they not perceive?"
  32,28,"And they say, “When will this decision take place, if you are truthful?”"
  32,29,"Proclaim, “On the Day of Decision*, the disbelievers will not benefit from their accepting faith, nor will they get respite.” (* Of death or of resurrection)"
  32,30,"Therefore turn away from them and wait – indeed they too have to wait."
